pageToken.description: Page token received from a previous `ListStreamObjectsRequest` call. Provide this to retrieve the subsequent page. When paginating, all other parameters provided to `ListStreamObjectsRequest` must match the call that provided the page token.

parent.description: Required. The parent stream that owns the collection of objects.

pageSize.description: Maximum number of objects to return. Default is 50. The maximum value is 1000; values above 1000 will be coerced to 1000.

object.description: Required. The name of the stream object resource to start a backfill job for.

startBackfillJob.description: Use this method to start a backfill job for the specified stream object.

name.description: Required. The name of the stream object resource to get.

get.description: Use this method to get details about a stream object.

stopBackfillJob.description: Use this method to stop a backfill job for the specified stream object.

object.description: Required. The name of the stream object resource to stop the backfill job for.
